This paper is about malware classification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for feature extraction and selection, which could potentially fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a per-class weighting paradigm, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of fusion techniques for combining different features, which could potentially fall under neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
